---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <main class="flex-grow flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-section px-6 md:px-12 w-full max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="max-w-4xl w-full mx-auto">
            <div class="text-center mb-xl">
                <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-brand-red mb-2 flex items-center justify-center gap-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <div class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant mb-2">Effective date: April 25, 2026</div>
                <p class="mt-4 opacity-90 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-on-surface-variant">Your privacy matters while you train your brain & typing skills.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-xl">

                <p class="text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed"><strong>Typpy</strong> (referred to as "we", "our", or "the Website") operates an interactive typing game designed to improve typing speed, accuracy, and cognitive focus. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website and participate in typing challenges. Please read this policy carefully. By using our game, you agree to the practices described below.</p>

                <div class="highlight-box bg-brand-red/10 border-l-4 border-brand-red p-lg rounded-2xl my-lg">
                    <p class="text-on-surface"><strong>Privacy-first approach:</strong> Our typing game is built to be fun and brain-enhancing without unnecessary data collection. Most gameplay data stays on your device unless you voluntarily interact with optional features (like saving high scores or contacting us).</p>
                </div>


                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">1. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We collect only the information that helps us improve the game experience, maintain security, and provide personalized training tools. The categories include:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 text-on-surface-variant">
                    <li><strong>Usage & Performance Data:</strong> When you play the typing game, we may collect typing speed (words per minute), accuracy percentage, reaction times, number of errors, and session duration. This data helps us fine-tune difficulty levels and offer brain training insights. This information is generally <strong>anonymized</strong> and not linked to your personal identity unless you provide identifiable details.</li>
                    <li><strong>Device & Technical Information:</strong> Standard internet log data such as IP address, browser type, operating system, device model, language preference, and timestamps. This improves compatibility and detects fraudulent activity.</li>
                    <li><strong>Local Storage & Cookies:</strong> We use browser local storage and small cookies to remember your game settings (e.g., theme, sound preferences, keyboard layout), track your personal best scores (stored only on your device by default), and to ensure game stability. No sensitive data is stored in cross-session tracking without consent.</li>
                    <li><strong>User-Provided Information (optional):</strong> If you contact us via email, participate in a leaderboard (if available), or sign up for optional user accounts (e.g., to save progress across devices), we may collect your email address, chosen username, and any message you send. Account features are entirely optional — you can fully enjoy the typing game without registration.</li>
                </ul>


                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">Any data we collect is used strictly to operate, analyze, and improve the typing brain training experience. Specifically, we may use information to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 text-on-surface-variant">
                    <li>Run and maintain the typing game interface and real-time performance feedback;</li>
                    <li>Generate aggregated statistics (e.g., average WPM across all players, most common typing errors) to improve game design and educational value;</li>
                    <li>Diagnose technical issues and enhance security against bots or malicious attacks;</li>
                    <li>Respond to user inquiries, support requests, or bug reports;</li>
                    <li>If you opt into leaderboards, we display your scores and chosen username publicly (no email or real identifying details);</li>
                    <li>Comply with legal obligations or enforce our terms of service.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We never sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties for marketing or advertising purposes.</p>


                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">3. Cookies & Local Storage – Your Choices</h2>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">Our game uses essential cookies and local storage to maintain your progress and preferences. These are strictly necessary for core functionality (e.g., remembering your in-game sound setting or current typing challenge progress). We do not use tracking cookies from third-party advertisers. You can disable cookies via your browser settings, but that may affect gameplay (some features like saving high scores might reset).</p>
                <div class="badge-list flex flex-wrap gap-2 my-md">
                      <span class="badge">Session cookies (temporary)</span>
                      <span class="badge">LocalStorage: game stats/scores</span>
                      <span class="badge">Functional preferences</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">Third-party analytics? At this stage, we may use privacy-focused, anonymized analytics (such as a self-hosted Plausible or similar) that does <strong>not</strong> collect personal data or use cookies. We will update this policy if we introduce any analytical tool with tracking identifiers.</p>


        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">4. Third-Party Services & Links</h2>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">The typing game is self-contained. However, our website may contain links to external resources (e.g., tutorials, support forums, or social media channels). Once you leave our domain, this Privacy Policy no longer applies. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party sites. We recommend reading their policies before providing any personal information.</p>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We do not integrate third-party advertising networks, meaning no targeted ads based on your gameplay habits. The focus remains purely on brain training.</p>


        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">5. Data Retention & Security</h2>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We retain anonymized gameplay metrics for as long as necessary to analyze performance trends and improve our game, typically up to 24 months for aggregated reports. Any personally identifiable data (like email inquiries or optional account information) is kept only as long as needed to resolve your request or maintain your account, and you can request deletion at any time.</p>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We implement reasonable security measures including encrypted connections (HTTPS), routine vulnerability scans, and restricted access to servers. While no internet transmission is 100% secure, we continually work to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.</p>


        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">6. Children’s Privacy (COPPA & GDPR-K)</h2>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">Our typing brain training game is suitable for all ages, but we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 (or under the age of digital consent in your jurisdiction, e.g., 16 in certain regions). If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal data (like an email address) without your consent, please contact us immediately. We will promptly delete such information. We encourage parents to supervise online activities to ensure a safe digital environment.</p>


                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">7. Your Privacy Rights (GDPR, CCPA, LGPD etc.)</h2>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 text-on-surface-variant">
                    <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> Request a copy of personal data we hold about you.</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Correct inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Erasure ("Right to be Forgotten"):</strong> Request deletion of your data, subject to legal obligations.</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Restrict or Object:</strong> Limit how we process your data in certain circumstances.</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Withdraw Consent:</strong> Where consent is required (e.g., optional account creation), you may withdraw it at any time.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">To exercise any of these rights, please send a verifiable request via the contact information below. We will respond within 30 days. No fee will be charged unless the request is excessive or repetitive. Also, California residents may ask for a notice of what personal information we share with third parties — we share none for cross-context behavioral advertising.</p>


                <div class="highlight-box bg-brand-red/10 border-l-4 border-brand-red p-lg rounded-2xl my-lg">
                    <p class="text-on-surface"><strong>Do Not Track (DNT) signals:</strong> Our website honors DNT browser settings. Since we don’t use cross-site tracking or targeted ads, we respect your preference for no tracking automatically.</p>
                </div>


        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">8. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">Our servers are located in secure data centers, currently within the [EU / United States / region placeholder] — please refer to your location. If you are accessing the typing game from outside that region, your information may be transferred to and processed in countries with different data protection laws. However, we ensure that appropriate safeguards (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) are applied to protect your data according to this Privacy Policy.</p>


        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our data practices, legal requirements, or game features. We will post any revised version on this page with an updated "Effective date". For significant changes, we may notify you via a notice on the website or by email if you have an account. We encourage you to review this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your privacy.</p>


                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">10. Contact Us</h2>
                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data handling practices, please reach out to our privacy team:</p>

                                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 text-on-surface-variant">
                                        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:rimbasystem@gmail.com" class="underline text-brand-red">rimbasystem@gmail.com</a></li>
                                        <!-- <li><strong>Contact Form:</strong> (accessible via our website's “Support” section)</li> -->
                                        <li><strong>Mailing Address (for formal correspondence):</strong> Sooonism Interactive Technology A-11-3 Mentari Condo, Jalan Sri Permaisuri 3, Bandar Tun Razak, 56000 Cheras, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia – (Only for written requests)</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="text-on-surface-variant mb-2">Please note: Rimba System is an IT systems / services owned by Sooonism Interactive Technology.</p>
                                <p class="text-on-surface-variant">We aim to respond to all legitimate requests within 15 business days.</p>


                <hr class="my-xl border-outline-variant">

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-md mt-xl">Quick Summary for Players</h2>
                <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-2xl p-lg mb-lg text-on-surface-variant">
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
                        <li><strong>What we track:</strong> Typing speed, accuracy, errors & device basics — to improve the training experience.</li>
                        <li><strong>No selling data:</strong> Your personal information is never sold or shared for ads.</li>
                        <li><strong>Optional accounts:</strong> You can play as a guest; no registration required.</li>
                        <li><strong>Minimal cookies:</strong> Only essential to remember game preferences & high scores locally.</li>
                        <li><strong>Your control:</strong> You can request data deletion or contact us anytime.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="footer-note text-center text-xs text-on-surface-variant mt-lg">
                    By using the typing game, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy. <br>
                    Your privacy is an integral part of our commitment to a secure and effective training experience.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
.highlight-box {
    /* Already styled with Tailwind above, but keep for legacy selectors */
}
.badge-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #facc15;
    color: #92400e;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95em;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 2px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.03);
}
.footer-note {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    opacity: 0.85;
}
</style>